<br>
 I don't think it'll be any time soon. I also don't know if we'll be able to live there indefinitely, because of the low G. Resorts and bases and such are fine, if you're not there too long, but long-term, living room is in free space.<br>
 Far, far more room for people to live. Planets and large moons are a tiny fraction of what's out there. Planets need to be in a very narrow range of conditions for us. Sure, we can terraform, but it'll take a long time to get conditions inferior to a space colony.<br>
<br>
 Heinlein used the term Lunies for the people on the Moon in the (excellent must-read) book &quot;the Moon is a Harsh Mistress&quot;. Good action (some of the best space combat stuff around), good everything.<br>
